<p>The <i><b>Temeraire</b></i> <a href="/wiki/Book_series" title="Book series">series</a> of <a href="/wiki/Novel" title="Novel">novels</a> by <a href="/wiki/Naomi_Novik" title="Naomi Novik">Naomi Novik</a>, is comprised of <i><a href="/wiki/His_Majesty%27s_Dragon" title="His Majesty's Dragon">His Majesty's Dragon</a></i> (released as <i>Temeraire</i> in the <a href="/wiki/United_Kingdom" title="United Kingdom">United Kingdom</a>), <i><a href="/wiki/Throne_of_Jade" title="Throne of Jade">Throne of Jade</a></i>, <i><a href="/wiki/Black_Powder_War" title="Black Powder War">Black Powder War</a></i>, <i><a href="/wiki/Empire_of_Ivory" title="Empire of Ivory">Empire of Ivory</a></i>, and <i><a href="/wiki/Victory_of_Eagles" title="Victory of Eagles">Victory of Eagles</a></i>. The novels are works of both <a href="/wiki/Fantasy" title="Fantasy">fantasy</a> and <a href="/wiki/Alternate_history" title="Alternate history">alternate history</a>: they are "a reimagining of the epic events of the <a href="/wiki/Napoleonic_Wars" title="Napoleonic Wars">Napoleonic Wars</a> with an <a href="/wiki/Air_Force" title="Air Force" class="mw-redirect">air force</a> â€” an air force of <a href="/wiki/Dragons" title="Dragons" class="mw-redirect">dragons</a>, manned by crews of aviators".<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
